  "description": "Enhance the Listening quiz results phase (frontend/src/pages/Listening.tsx) so that for each incorrectly answered question users can instantly re-hear the supporting passage sentence at a slower rate (0.75x) — a high-value review loop that turns mistakes into targeted listening practice. Currently the results screen lists results with explanations but offers no audio review path; users must replay the entire passage. Implementation:\n\n1. In Listening.tsx, persist the passage and sentences (already available via extractSentences(passage)) into the results phase render.\n2. Add a small helper findRelevantSentenceIndex(question, options[correctIndex], sentences) that scores each sentence by overlap of meaningful tokens (lowercase, length>=4, stopword filtered) with the correct option text and the question text, returning the highest-scoring index (fallback: 0). Place this helper in a new file frontend/src/utils/listeningReview.ts and unit-test it in frontend/src/__tests__/listeningReview.test.ts (cases: exact keyword match, no overlap fallback, tie-breaking by question overlap).\n3. In the results phase JSX, for every result where selectedIndex !== correctIndex, render a button '🔊 Replay sentence (0.75x)' that calls a new replayReviewSentence(idx) function which cancels current speech, creates a SpeechSynthesisUtterance with rate=0.75, lang='en-US', and tracks a playingReviewIdx state to show a small pulsing indicator while playing. Also add a 'Show sentence' toggle that reveals the sentence text under the button.\n4. Add a top-level 'Replay all missed sentences' button at the top of the results section that sequentially plays each missed sentence (chained via utterance.onend).\n5. Ensure speechSynthesis.cancel() runs on phase change / unmount (existing cleanup already covers unmount; extend to phase transition out of results).\n\nNo backend or schema changes. Files: frontend/src/pages/Listening.tsx, frontend/src/utils/listeningReview.ts, frontend/src/__tests__/listeningReview.test.ts. This builds directly on the recent listening quiz tracking work (iter 631) by closing the feedback loop with audio review.",
