  "description": "PERF win for the conversation endpoint. The original PERF-HIGH backlog item (4) — parallelize feedback+reply with asyncio.gather — is ALREADY IMPLEMENTED in app/routers/conversation.py send_message (lines 568-589). To make further p50 progress, skip the grammar-check LLM call entirely when the user's message is trivial: too short to meaningfully grammar-check or a pure acknowledgment. This removes one LLM round-trip (~2-4s) from a common case and is trivial to test.\n\n**Change in app/routers/conversation.py (send_message, around lines 566-589):**\n1. Add a small module-level helper `_should_skip_grammar_check(text: str) -> bool` that returns True when:\n   - The trimmed message has fewer than 4 word tokens (split on whitespace after stripping punctuation), OR\n   - The lowercased trimmed message (with trailing punctuation stripped) is in a small set of pure acknowledgments: {'yes','no','ok','okay','sure','thanks','thank you','yeah','yep','nope','cool','great','nice','hi','hello','hey','bye','goodbye','right','exactly','maybe','same','me too'}.\n2. In send_message, before constructing the parallel gather, compute `skip_grammar = _should_skip_grammar_check(req.content)`. If True, replace the `_safe_grammar_check` task with an `asyncio.sleep(0)`-style no-op that returns None, and log `latency_tracker`-friendly info `'skipping grammar check (trivial message)'`. The reply LLM call still runs. The rest of the flow is unchanged: `feedback` will be None and the existing `if feedback is not None:` branch already handles that.\n3. Keep behavior identical when message is non-trivial.\n\n**Tests in tests/unit/test_conversation_skip_grammar.py (new file):**\n- Unit-test `_should_skip_grammar_check` directly with: '', 'yes', 'Yes!', 'ok.', 'thank you', 'I am hungry today' (False — 4+ words), 'hi there friend' (False — 3 words but not in ack set, actually returns True since <4; document the rule), 'I went to the store yesterday and bought apples' (False).\n- Integration test (tests/integration/test_conversation_skip_grammar.py): mock copilot service so `ask` returns 'AI reply' and `ask_json` raises if called. POST to /api/conversation/start then /api/conversation/message with content='yes'. Assert response 200, feedback is None, and ask_json was NOT called. Then send a long message and assert ask_json IS called.\n\nNo schema changes. No frontend changes (feedback:null is already a supported response shape — see `Reply helpers ... fetched lazily` comment, and the frontend already tolerates null feedback from /helpers fallback).",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/routers/conversation.py", "tests/unit/test_conversation_skip_grammar.py", "tests/integration/test_conversation_skip_grammar.py"],
